From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Morandini <daniel.morandini@keepinmind.info>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 10:03:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fftools/ffmpeg_demux: fix copyts MPEG-TS wrap on subtitles
To: ffmpeg-devel@ffmpeg.org

The copyts MPEG-TS wrap heuristic in ts_discontinuity_detect() previously
reused the normal discontinuity-correction branch when adding one timestamp
wrap to a packet DTS made it close to the expected next DTS. That branch
snaps pkt->dts to ds->next_dts.

For regularly paced audio/video streams that is usually close enough. For
sparse subtitle streams, especially DVB teletext and DVB subtitle streams
whose timestamps are derived from PCR, that snap can collapse adjacent
packets onto a single timestamp. Once libavformat's wrap_timestamp() stops
adjusting raw timestamps after they climb back past pts_wrap_reference, the
subtitle DTS can regress by exactly 2^pts_wrap_bits. Downstream muxers then
emit Non-monotonic DTS warnings and clamp the subtitle clock.

Handle confirmed copyts MPEG-TS wraps directly: add one wrap period to the
packet DTS and PTS, preserve the packet's spacing within the wrap epoch, and
return without running the normal discontinuity branch. Audio/video continue
to enter the detector as before. Subtitle streams enter it only under
-copyts, which keeps non-copyts subtitle behavior unchanged while covering
the MPEG-TS rollover case.

Reproduced with synthetic MPEG-TS fixtures containing video PCR plus DVB
subtitle and DVB teletext subtitle PIDs. Without this change the last two
subtitle packets are clamped at 15784527392. With this change they advance
to 15789945392 and 15789997592. The matching FATE targets
fate-mpegts-copyts-subtitle-wrap and fate-mpegts-copyts-teletext-wrap pass.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Morandini <daniel.morandini@keepinmind.info>
---
 fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c | 30 +++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c b/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
index 99f5cfc2c5..95cd5e1a63 100644
--- a/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
+++ b/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
@@ -234,13 +234,29 @@ static void ts_discontinuity_detect(Demuxer *d, InputStream *ist,
     int64_t pkt_dts = av_rescale_q_rnd(pkt->dts, pkt->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
                                        AV_ROUND_NEAR_INF | AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
 
+    // copyts MPEG-TS wrap: libavformat's wrap_timestamp() handles only the first
+    // wrap and stops once raw timestamps climb back past pts_wrap_reference. For
+    // continued operation across many wraps under -copyts, add exactly one wrap
+    // period when the packet's timestamp + one wrap matches the expected next dts
+    // far more closely than the raw timestamp does. Direct addition preserves
+    // inter-packet timing within the wrap epoch, which matters for sparse
+    // subtitle streams where snap-to-next_dts would collapse adjacent packets.
     if (copy_ts && ds->next_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
         fmt_is_discont && ist->st->pts_wrap_bits < 60) {
-        int64_t wrap_dts = av_rescale_q_rnd(pkt->dts + (1LL<<ist->st->pts_wrap_bits),
+        int64_t wrap = 1LL << ist->st->pts_wrap_bits;
+        int64_t wrap_dts = av_rescale_q_rnd(pkt->dts + wrap,
                                             pkt->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
                                             AV_ROUND_NEAR_INF|AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
-        if (FFABS(wrap_dts - ds->next_dts) < FFABS(pkt_dts - ds->next_dts)/10)
-            disable_discontinuity_correction = 0;
+        if (FFABS(wrap_dts - ds->next_dts) < FFABS(pkt_dts - ds->next_dts)/10) {
+            pkt->dts += wrap;
+            if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
+                pkt->pts += wrap;
+            av_log(ist, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
+                   "MPEG-TS pts wrap (stream id=%d): added %"PRId64" tick wrap\n",
+                   ist->st->id, wrap);
+            d->last_ts = av_rescale_q(pkt->dts, pkt->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
+            return;
+        }
     }
 
     if (ds->next_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && !disable_discontinuity_correction) {
@@ -305,9 +321,13 @@ static void ts_discontinuity_process(Demuxer *d, InputStream *ist,
     if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
         pkt->pts += offset;
 
-    // detect timestamp discontinuities for audio/video
+    // detect timestamp discontinuities for audio/video. Under -copyts, subtitle
+    // streams in AVFMT_TS_DISCONT containers need the same MPEG-TS wrap
+    // correction because libavformat's wrap_timestamp() stops once raw
+    // timestamps climb back past pts_wrap_reference.
     if ((ist->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
-         ist->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) &&
+         ist->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
+         (copy_ts && ist->par->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE)) &&
         pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
         ts_discontinuity_detect(d, ist, pkt);
 }
